title: IN PHOTOS: Stars at Panagbenga Festival 2017
text:
Entertainment News IN PHOTOS: Stars at Panagbenga Festival 2017 Bea Alonzo, Enchong Dee, Jericho Rosales, Kylie Verzosa and more take part in the annual flower festival in Baguio Published 2:43   2:52   A LOVE TO LAST FLOAT. Bea Alonzo and Enchong Dee wave to the crowd at the Panagbenga festival in Baguio. The two are part of the show 'A Love To Last.' Photo by Mau Victa/Rappler 
BAGUIO CITY â€“ The annual Panagbenga Festival started on Saturday, February 25 and some of our favorite stars celebrated with the people of Baguio on Sunday, February 26, during the flower parade. ( [IN PHOTOS] Nurturing nature: Panagbenga 2017 street dance parade ) 
A Love to Last stars Bea Alonzo and Enchong Dee participated in the the float sponsored by ABS-CBN. Photo by Ivan Jim Layugan /Rappler Photo by Ivan Jim Layugan /Rappler A post shared by STAR CREATIVES (@starcreativestv) on Feb 25, 2017 at 7:44pm PST 
Jericho Rosales was also present at the Panagbenga Festival and had a photo with Bea and Enchong. Photo by Ivan Jim Layugan /Rappler A post shared by STAR CREATIVES (@starcreativestv) on Feb 25, 2017 at 5:59pm PST 
The love team of Alden Richards and Maine "Yaya Dub" Mendoza or AlDub was also present at the festival. The two are set to star in their first teleserye entitled Destined To Be Yours , which will air on Monday, February 27. Photo by Ivan Jim Layugan /Rappler Photo By Mau Victa/Rappler
